20:55.297 --> 20:59.384
And, Walter, I'm losing,
circulation in my arms.

20:59.384 --> 21:01.345
Okay, no, good. Good.

21:01.345 --> 21:03.472
This is good.
This is why we do dress rehearsals.

21:03.472 --> 21:05.974
- Okay. Yes.
- And you look fantastic.

21:05.974 --> 21:08.685
This dress would be fantastic
on a midsize child.

21:09.394 --> 21:10.395
I'm an adult woman.

21:10.395 --> 21:13.649
Good. I love that energy. And, you know--

21:13.649 --> 21:15.025
Could we get bigger cards?

21:15.025 --> 21:18.028
No, It's not that I can't read it.

21:18.028 --> 21:20.531
It's that my conscience
won't let me read that.

21:20.531 --> 21:23.450
I have my own thing prepared.
May I? Or I will.

21:33.293 --> 21:36.505
- Three, two, one?
- You can just talk.

21:36.505 --> 21:37.589
Okay.

21:39.925 --> 21:42.761
I'm Elizabeth Zott,
and this is <i>Supper at Six</i>.

21:42.761 --> 21:44.847
Baking powder is an alkali

21:44.847 --> 21:47.140
that will raise the pH levels
of your chicken skin

21:47.140 --> 21:49.268
and will result in a crisp texture.

21:50.644 --> 21:51.728
I'm gonna take that back.

21:51.728 --> 21:53.438
- Okay, Elizabeth...
- I'm E-- Yes?

21:53.438 --> 21:57.526
...if you make a mistake, just keep going.
It's-- 'Cause the show is live.

21:57.526 --> 22:00.487
- So, you know, we can't go back.
- That's right. Yes. My apologies.

22:00.487 --> 22:03.866
That's right. Okay.

22:05.993 --> 22:06.994
All right.

22:07.494 --> 22:11.164
As I was saying,
baking powder is a leavening agent

22:11.164 --> 22:13.584
which elevates the pH of the chicken skin.

22:13.584 --> 22:17.671
In short,
the skin expands when you cook it.

22:17.671 --> 22:20.966
<i>The more surface area,
the crispier the texture.</i>

22:21.550 --> 22:24.386
- <i>Allow me to demonstrate...</i>
- The skin's pH level? Is this a joke?

22:24.386 --> 22:26.722
We're still finding the show's voice.

22:26.722 --> 22:30.475
Big hair, tight dress, homey set. Check.

22:30.475 --> 22:34.396
But we need a sexy wife,
loving mother that every man loves to see

22:34.396 --> 22:36.398
when he comes home from work.

22:36.398 --> 22:41.695
But this time, we aim to shrink
the square unit of our vegetables.

22:41.695 --> 22:45.032
Square unit? What the fuck is this?

22:46.325 --> 22:48.118
Phil. Look.

22:49.286 --> 22:51.330
I mean, the thing is,

22:51.330 --> 22:54.833
not only is she a cook and a mother,
but she is also a chemist.

22:54.833 --> 22:57.961
So I was thinking let's--
let's play up her credentials,

22:57.961 --> 23:00.589
give housewives someone to aspire to.

23:00.589 --> 23:02.591
