- What are those?

23:02.591 --> 23:04.843
<i>Which is why I prefer goggles,</i>

23:04.843 --> 23:07.137
<i>which are woefully absent
from cookware sets.</i>

23:07.137 --> 23:10.891
Phil, I think we can make
something meaningful here.

23:10.891 --> 23:14.520
Meaningful? What are you, Amish? No!

23:14.520 --> 23:18.023
We want tight dresses,
suggestive movements,

23:18.023 --> 23:21.693
like the way she dons her potholders
just so.

23:22.361 --> 23:25.822
And at the end of every show,
she should make her husband a cocktail.

23:26.406 --> 23:27.824
I don't think Miss Zott

23:27.824 --> 23:30.702
- is gonna be willing to--
- Why the fuck would I care what she wants?

23:31.703 --> 23:32.829
It's her show.

23:33.330 --> 23:36.083
No, Walter. It's my show.

23:41.547 --> 23:42.923
Hi, Six Thirty.

23:48.136 --> 23:49.721
<i>Welcome home, Mad.</i>

23:49.721 --> 23:53.600
<i>Here's your schedule for today.
3:30 to 4:00 p.m., snack time.</i>

23:54.101 --> 23:55.602
<i>There are deviled eggs in the fridge.</i>

23:55.602 --> 23:58.897
<i>Suggestion: They're better
with a little paprika sprinkled on top.</i>

24:02.526 --> 24:04.945
<i>4:00 to 4:30 p.m., homework.</i>

24:07.573 --> 24:10.659
<i>I always liked to do whatever
my least favorite subject was first.</i>

24:11.743 --> 24:12.911
<i>It gets it out of the way.</i>

24:16.039 --> 24:18.542
<i>4:30 to 5:00 p.m., reading.</i>

24:19.501 --> 24:23.797
<i>Read</i> Great Expectations <i>to Six Thirty.
