so it's useless.

27:56.134 --> 27:57.386
See the winged bull?

27:58.595 --> 28:00.138
That's how they draw St. Luke.

28:00.138 --> 28:02.516
Your dad went to a school
called St. Luke's.

28:04.268 --> 28:06.979
Now, which St. Luke's?

28:07.938 --> 28:09.022
That's the question.

28:10.816 --> 28:17.781
<i>Do not pass me by</i>

28:25.581 --> 28:27.207
And that concludes our time.

28:27.207 --> 28:30.919
Tomorrow on <i>Supper at Six</i>,
we will study colloids.

28:30.919 --> 28:33.005
Although, I don't know why
the show is called <i>Supper at Six</i>.

28:33.005 --> 28:36.967
It should be called <i>Supper at 5:30</i>.
But here we are.

28:37.467 --> 28:42.306
Walter, we need to discuss the title.
It's incredibly misleading.

28:42.306 --> 28:47.060
Well, we can discuss that.
And I just-- Let's have a drink.

28:47.060 --> 28:48.520
I don't really drink.

28:48.520 --> 28:50.189
- I do.
- Okay.

28:50.772 --> 28:53.483
I know what you're going to say,
and adjustments will be made.

28:53.483 --> 28:54.776
I took notes.

28:55.360 --> 28:59.823
The set: altogether too cluttered.
Cue cards: unnecessary, eliminate.

28:59.823 --> 29:04.703
Wardrobe: Walter, this dress is obscene,
and I need my lab coat.

29:07.206 --> 29:08.832
- What? You won't consider a lab coat?
- Elizabeth.

29:08.832 --> 29:10.542
It has more surface area than an apron.

29:10.542 --> 29:12.628
I don't understand
why everyone doesn't cook in a lab coat.

29:12.628 --> 29:14.796
Elizabeth, it's not about the lab coat.

29:17.090 --> 29:18.967
Phil hated the show.

29:20.135 --> 29:22.304
Phil? Who's Phil?

29:22.304 --> 29:24.598
He's the station owner.

29:24.598 --> 29:27.559
I hate him. I hate him so much.

29:27.559 --> 29:32.773
He haunts me in my dreams.
He haunts me when I'm awake.

29:33.565 --> 29:36.235
Do I care what Phil thinks?

29:36.235 --> 29:38.278
- No, I do not.
- But...

29:39.988 --> 29:44.618
I agree with him.
We do need to make some changes.

29:44.618 --> 29:46.662
I knew this was going to happen, Walter.

29:46.662 --> 29:50.082
- You said that this would be my show.
- Yeah, and it is. It is.

29:51.250 --> 29:52.543
So make it yours.

29:55.963 --> 29:57.339
You know what I love about TV?

30:01.677 --> 30:02.678
Everything.

30:03.679 --> 30:09.309
It has the power to transport
and entertain.

30:10.269 --> 30:13.355
It can make you feel a part of something.

30:15.148 --> 30:20.696
The problem with the show today wasn't
a set problem or a wardrobe problem.

30:20.696 --> 30:26.660
It's more I wanted to see you be you.
Not just a scientist.

30:26.660 --> 30:29.371
But I am a scientist. That is who I am.

30:29.371 --> 30:30.956
That may be.

30:32.249 --> 30:34.877
But that's only a start.

30:49.266 --> 30:53.395
Mrs. Mudford said I've been doing
really, really well in class.

30:53.395 --> 30:58.859
I bit my tongue till it bled when she
had us draw penguins with coats and hats.

30:58.859 --> 31:00.360
I guess she doesn't know

31:00.360 --> 31:04.031
that many groups of penguins
actually live below the equator.

31:04.031 --> 31:05.741
Well, that is a common misconception.

31:05.741 --> 31:08.285
And I haven't asked the librarian
for a single book!

31:08.285 --> 31:09.286
And at the cafeteria,

31:09.286 --> 31:11.413
- I didn't share my lunch with Amanda--
- Mad.

31:11.413 --> 31:13.665
I understand that you're nervous
about switching schools.

31:13.665 --> 31:16.335
But change is good. Change is evolution.

31:17.211 --> 31:19.671
We're gonna split up. Do you wanna do
the butcher counter or dairy?

31:20.255 --> 31:21.965
Can't I just stay with you?

31:24.676 --> 31:25.969
Sure, bunny.

31:38.315 --> 31:39.191
Come in.

31:40.317 --> 31:43.570
So, small, tiny, little change in plans.

31:43.570 --> 31:45.906
- Nothing big.
- Yes?

31:45.906 --> 31:47.282
Really barely perceptible.

31:47.282 --> 31:48.450
Walter.

31:49.034 --> 31:50.118
We--

31:51.078 --> 31:53.956
<i>Supper at Six</i> is airing tonight.
Today. Right now.

31:54.790 --> 31:57.376
On TV? But we still have
two more weeks of rehearsals.

31:57.376 --> 32:01.296
The reruns of the show
that you replaced are not performing.

32:01.296 --> 32:03.131
And here's the thing.
Here's the good news.

32:03.131 --> 32:05.259
And I maybe should've said this earlier.

32:05.259 --> 32:09.346
We're the lowest-rated channel,
so very few people will be tuned in.

32:09.346 --> 32:11.098
And Phil hates us,

32:11.098 --> 32:13.809
and he actually may be doing this
as a reason to cancel the show.

32:14.393 --> 32:18.063
So when you said you liaise with talent,
is this what you were referring to?

32:18.063 --> 32:19.648
I did not say I was good at it.

32:21.775 --> 32:22.776
Break a leg.

32:23.277 --> 32:24.361
I am considering it.

32:31.535 --> 32:34.663
Testing. Testing.
One, two, three.

32:34.663 --> 32:37.958
Testing. Testing. One, two, three.

32:41.837 --> 32:43.755
Shari, take note of this placement.

32:44.715 --> 32:47.634
Let's go! Let's go, people!

32:48.302 --> 32:50.888
Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!

32:53.390 --> 32:57.895
We're live in five, four, three, two, one.

33:14.203 --> 33:17.331
I take cooking seriously,
and I know you do too.

33:17.998 --> 33:21.293
I also know that your time is precious,
and, well, so is mine.

33:21.293 --> 33:24.838
Is that a fucking pencil?
What does she need a fucking pencil for?

33:24.838 --> 33:28.467
In my experience, people do not appreciate
the work and sacrifice

33:28.467 --> 33:31.470
that goes into being
a mother, a wife, a woman.

33:32.262 --> 33:33.931
Well, I am not one of those people.

33:34.515 --> 33:37.935
At the end of our time here together,
we will have done something worth doing.

33:38.602 --> 33:41.563
We will have created
something that will not go unnoticed.

33:41.563 --> 33:44.107
We will have made supper,
and it will matter.

33:46.235 --> 33:48.403
I prefer to have room
when I'm doing my work.

33:48.403 --> 33:51.865
It reinforces that the work we're doing
together is important.

33:53.408 --> 33:55.244
Harry, would you mind helping me
clear these things?

33:55.244 --> 33:57.829
And Eugene, Amos. Thank you.

34:09.842 --> 34:12.678
Cooking is chemistry,
and chemistry is life.

34:12.678 --> 34:16.681
Your ability to change everything,
including yourself, starts here.

34:17.641 --> 34:18.725
Let's begin, shall we?

34:27.400 --> 34:28.819
<i>What worked for you with the show?</i>

34:29.527 --> 34:32.697
I'm an insomniac,
and it put me right to sleep.

34:34.324 --> 34:38.661
Potatoes are rich in vitamin C,
potassium and complex carbohydrates.

34:38.661 --> 34:41.831
I stand proudly with
the overlooked workhorse of the kitchen:

34:41.831 --> 34:43.667
women and baked potatoes.

34:44.251 --> 34:45.752
Yes?

34:45.752 --> 34:48.547
- I actually thought that she was--
- Would it have killed her to smile?

34:48.547 --> 34:51.257
Totally.
And it looks like she's got a good figure,

34:51.257 --> 34:53.010
but she's hiding it
behind that weird coat.

34:53.010 --> 34:56.471
I am putting cinnamon in my chili.
I've never done that before.

34:56.972 --> 34:59.057
Don't be afraid to experiment
in the kitchen.

34:59.558 --> 35:02.644
Fearlessness in the kitchen
equates to fearlessness in life.

35:03.478 --> 35:06.106
Describe how you felt watching
the show in one word.

35:06.857 --> 35:08.525
- Bored.
- Punished.

35:08.525 --> 35:11.069
- Drained. Depressed.
- Saddened. Lost.

35:11.862 --> 35:12.863
Yes, your word?

35:13.530 --> 35:14.364
Capable.

35:15.324 --> 35:17.117
Capable?
What the hell does that even mean?

35:23.790 --> 35:25.626
And that is all we have time for today.

35:25.626 --> 35:26.960
I hope you'll join me tomorrow

35:26.960 --> 35:29.296
as we explore
the fascinating world of temperature

35:29.296 --> 35:31.507
